CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1962, pg. 5, reads: "Made Quick Arrest - Patrolman Leon Rhodes (left), was recently cited for teaming with his radio police patrol car accomplice, Ptm. Orlando Diggs (not in pictured) for apprehending and arresting, within ten minutes after, the suspect in hold-up of Paulston St. grocery. Smiling with Ptm. Rhodes (above) is Ptm. Chandler Sermons, his usual patrol car mate, who was off duty on the day of the quick apprehension.  The suspect, Orville Taylor, 67 Arthur St., has been indicted. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Police officers Leon Rhodes and Chandler Sermons standing beside City of Pittsburgh police cruiser on residential street
